Note = {World Conference on Information Systems and Technologies (WorldCIST), La
   Toja Island, SPAIN, APR 16-19, 2019},
Abstract = {Relation Extraction (RE) is part of Information Extraction (IE) and aims
   to obtain instances of semantic relations in textual documents. The
   countless possibilities of relations, the myriad of subjects, the
   difficulty in identifying emotions and the amount of unstructured and
   heterogeneous data, have challenged the researchers to define innovative
   and even more accurate methodologies. This paper presents the evaluation
   results obtained with a set of RE systems on identifying semantic
   relations in criminal police reports. We have evaluated different
   applications with documents in English and Portuguese. The results
   obtained give us useful insights to continue the research work, and to
   design the relation extraction system applied to related domain.},
