Note = {3rd Doctoral Symposium on Computational Intelligence (DoSCI), Inst of
   Eng and Tech, Lucknow, INDIA, MAR 05, 2022},
Abstract = {Smart cities use various technologies and applications to improve
   performance of services: health, education, transportation, energy,
   etc., in order to achieve the required level of sustainability, and to
   improve their citizens' living standards. As a result, data in huge
   amounts are generated which are used in useful application areas. One of
   the modern technologies that contribute to enhancing the services of
   smart city is big data analysis using Hadoop MapReduce where it is a
   powerful computational model that is more popular among all big data
   tools. This paper proposes the Hadoop MapReduce-based system to deal
   with big data by classifying the population of the smart city according
   to their behaviors (the good works and bad works), where these data
   taken from various resources with different categories which include
   good, non-guilty, guilty, suspect, fugitive, criminal, incriminatory,
   wanted. The proposed system supports a reinhabitate system to deal with
   these categories to improve the behavior of people.},
