Abstract = {A crime, often known as a criminal offence, is an act that harms not
   just people but also a community, society, or state. Every second, a
   large number of crimes occur in various locations, patterns, and times,
   and the number continues to rise. Murder, retaliation, theft, rape,
   kidnapping, and burglary are only a few examples of many sorts of
   crimes. As a result, it's critical to recognise various reasons and
   criminal patterns. This study examines how machine learning algorithms
   may be created and analysed to classify crimes as high, medium, or low
   based on real-time parameters such as single parent crime, health, and
   crime rate, punished crime.},
