   (SmartWorld/SCALCOM/UIC/ATC/CBDCom/IOP/SCI), San Francisco, CA, AUG
   04-08, 2017},
Organization = {IEEE; IEEE Comp Soc; IEEE Computat Intelligence Soc; IEEE TCSC},
Abstract = {San-Francisco in the US and Natal in Brazil are two coastal cities which
   are known rather for its tech scene and natural beauty than for its
   criminal activities. We analyze characteristics of the urban environment
   in these two cities, deploying a machine learning model to detect
   categories and hotspots of criminal activities. We propose an extensive
   set of spatio-temporal \& urban features which can significantly improve
   the accuracy of machine learning models for these tasks, one of which
   achieved Top 1\% performance on a Crime Classification Competition by
   kaggle. com. Extensive evaluation on several years of crime records from
   both cities show how some features such as the street network - carry
   important information about criminal activities.},
