Number = {15},
Pages = {21127-21152},
Month = {DEC},
Abstract = {In this manuscript proposes an efficient hybrid approach for home energy
   management with distribution system based on Internet of things (IoT).
   The proposed hybrid approach is the joint execution of Forensic-Based
   Investigation (FBI) and Isolation Forest, hence named as FBI-iForest
   approach. The main purpose of the proposed method is to optimally manage
   the power and resources of the distribution system. The proposed
   approach considers two main factors like user satisfaction and cost of
   energy utilization. The proposed approach is designed under the
   environment of smart grid, which consists of photovoltaic (PV), wind
   turbine (WT), micro turbine (MT), and battery. The household appliance
   management is one of the important factors for smart grid system for
   cost saving purpose. The proposed system, data acquisition module of IoT
   is interfaced to every home appliance provides an IP address. The demand
   response of each device is collected by the IoT object transmitted to
   the centralized server. The transmitted data is operated through the
   FBIiForest approach. The IoT-based energy management provides
   flexibility of these networks as well as optimum use of available
   resources. At last, the proposed model is realized on MATLAB/Simulink
   platform. The cost of the proposed method for case 1, 2 and 3 achieves
   \$2.8, \$340 and \$1100.},
