Organization = {IEEE, Syst Man \& Cybernet Soc},
Abstract = {Most law enforcement agencies today are faced with enormous quantities
   of data that must be processed and turned into useful information. Two
   technologies provide the means to turn data into information: data
   fusion and data mining. Data fusion organizes, combines, and interprets
   information from multiple sources, and it overcomes confusion from
   conflicting reports and cluttered or noisy backgrounds. Data mining is
   concerned with the automatic discovery of patterns and relationships in
   large databases. This paper describes ReCAP, the Regional Crime Analysis
   Program that was built to provide crime analysts with both technologies.},
